Mapping on db

  • 0.1 Overall alignment rates
  • 0.2 Construct a table for all samples

The reads obtained after WGA or WTA from each library were mapped against the reference panel.

0.1 Overall alignment rates

Lets look at the overall alignment rates:

stats=read.table("../mapping_wga-wta_on_db/stats_alignment.txt", h=FALSE, sep=":")
names(stats)=c("file", "alignt_rate")
head(stats)
sample_number=strsplit(stats$file, "_")
sample_number=unlist(lapply(X = sample_number, FUN = function(x){
  res=strsplit(x[2], ".", fixed=T)[[1]][1]
  return(res)
}))
stats$sample = as.numeric(sample_number)
stats=stats[order(stats$sample),]
head(stats)
hist(stats$alignt_rate, xlab="overall alignement rate")

barplot(stats$alignt_rate, horiz = T, names.arg = stats$sample, cex.names = 0.2, las=1)

summary(stats$alignt_rate)
   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
   0.00   58.46   68.66   66.51   79.19   94.08

0.2 Construct a table for all samples

# read all 112 files and concatenate

filenames=list.files("../mapping_wga-wta_on_db/", pattern="*.table.txt", full.names = TRUE)
head(filenames)
[1] "../mapping_wga-wta_on_db//sample_100.table.txt" "../mapping_wga-wta_on_db//sample_101.table.txt"
[3] "../mapping_wga-wta_on_db//sample_102.table.txt" "../mapping_wga-wta_on_db//sample_103.table.txt"
[5] "../mapping_wga-wta_on_db//sample_104.table.txt" "../mapping_wga-wta_on_db//sample_105.table.txt"
datalist = lapply(filenames, function(x){
  res=read.table(file=x,comment.char = "", header=T)
  res=res[,c("X.rname", "coverage")]
  sample=strsplit(x, split = "//", fixed = TRUE)[[1]][2]
  sample=strsplit(sample, split = ".table", fixed = TRUE)[[1]][1]
  names(res)=c("contig", sample)
  #sort accordint to contig name
  res=res[order(res$contig),]
  return(res)
    }
  )
length(datalist)
[1] 112
data_merged=do.call(cbind.data.frame,datalist)
head(data_merged)
# remove contig cols
rownames(data_merged)=data_merged$contig
data_merged=data_merged[, grep(pattern = "sample", x = names(data_merged))]
head(data_merged)

Append relevant information (location, sampling date, species) for each sample

infos=read.table("/Users/jvaraldi/Documents/Manips/Viromics_Metagenomics/Sample_info.txt", fill=T, h=T, sep="\t")
dim(infos)
[1] 112  10
head(infos)
# there are some hidden spaces to remove
infos=as.data.frame(apply(infos, 2, function(x) {sub(pattern = " ", replacement = "", x)}))
head(infos)
# create a short informative name for each sample
lib_type=unlist(lapply(X = infos$Sample.ID, FUN = function(x){
    if(grepl(pattern = "WTA", x))
      "WTA"
  else
  if (grepl(pattern = "WGA", x))
    "WGA"
}))
infos$lib_type=lib_type

short_name=paste(infos$species_corrected, infos$location, infos$year, infos$month, infos$lib_type, sep="_")

# check length
length(unique(short_name))
[1] 110
# this is because a sample was taken as D. phalerata but was in fact D. im. So We have two samples from D.im Gotheron September 2012 (both for WGA and WTA).
short_name[short_name=="D.im_Gotheron_2012_Sept_WGA"]
[1] "D.im_Gotheron_2012_Sept_WGA" "D.im_Gotheron_2012_Sept_WGA"
# let's call the second bis
short_name[short_name=="D.im_Gotheron_2012_Sept_WGA"][2]="D.im_Gotheron_2012_Sept_WGAbis"
short_name[short_name=="D.im_Gotheron_2012_Sept_WTA"][2]="D.im_Gotheron_2012_Sept_WTAbis"

# check length
length(unique(short_name))
[1] 112
Sample=paste("sample", infos$Sample,sep =  "_")

infos=data.frame(infos, short_name)
infos$Sample=Sample

# modify sample names 
infos2=merge(x = names(data_merged), y = infos, by.x="x", by.y="Sample")
head(infos2)
# write to disk
write.table(infos2, file = "../TABLES/infos2.txt", col.names = TRUE, row.names = FALSE, quote=FALSE, sep="\t")

names(data_merged)=infos2$short_name

# divide by 100 to have proportions (instead of %)
data_merged=data_merged/100
dim(data_merged)
[1] 23182   112
head(data_merged)

Subset to contigs with at least one sample with coverage > 0.001.

data_merged_filtered=data_merged[-which(apply(X = data_merged, MARGIN = 1, FUN = max)<0.001),]
dim(data_merged_filtered)
[1] 5382  112

write tables to disk

write.table(data_merged, file = "../TABLES/coverage_raw.txt", quote=FALSE, sep="\t")

write.table(data_merged_filtered, file = "../TABLES/coverage_filtered.txt", quote=FALSE, sep="\t")

Looks nice, as expected we find LbFV motly in Leptopilina boulardi (see bma files for the other samples) and LhFV only in Leptopilina heterotoma, with a few exception (see bam files to confirm that this corresponds to valuable alignements).
